===subject:Reply to Federalist
===from:Ursula Davis
===date:Sat Feb  8 17:52:50 2003
===message:Although our government seems the fairest to us compared to others, it is by not means perfect.  Some of the fears of the Anti-Federalist came true.  Why is it that those in the Senate are so wealthy and receive the perks that they do.  Is that fair to the person who is making minimum wage.  Is our government truly representative of our society.  How may women are minorities are represented and for how long have they been a part of our government.  The Constitution is very open to interpretation like the law and the Bible.  Who gets to interpret it becomes the issue.  The Anti-Federalist were right to be cautious.  Their main concern was that this new form of Government would not work and either state or national government would dominate and the people would suffer.  Remember, the Anti-Federalist pushed for the Bill of Rights to be added.  Without it, how much freedom from government rule do you think we would really have?
=========yorg=========
