===message:You are correct when you say that a weak national government would have left America open to foreign attack, especially by Britain.  Even with the national government, Britain did attack us and we defeated them in the War of 1812 (1812-1814).  If America didn't have a national government, even the infant one that they had at the time, they most likely wouldn't have been able to defend themselves as well.  The states would have squabbled amongst themselves until it was too late to mount a decent defense.
=========yorg=========
